        optionFeedback: [`Antinuclear antibodies are seen in lupus and other autoimmune diseases. Lupus nephritis does not present as crescentic glomerulonephritis with acute renal failure. `,`The acute presentation of oliguria and renal failure, and the histologic appearance of crescentic glomerulonephritis, are characteristic of rapidly progressive glomerulonephritis (RPGN). This clinical syndrome has numerous possible underlying causes, the most common of which is Goodpasture syndrome, which is associated with the deposition of anti-GBM antibody in the glomerulus in a linear immunofluorescence pattern. `,`Immune-complex glomerulonephritis is a rare complication of HIV disease. It does not usually present as crescentic glomerulonephritis.  HIV disease is typically associated with focal sclerosing glomerulosclerosis  `,`Measurements of total serum immunoglobulin would not be helpful for the diagnosis.`,``],
