        q: `A 7-year-old boy has become less active over the past 10 days. On physical examination, he has facial puffiness. Urinalysis shows no blood, glucose, or ketones, and microscopic examination shows no casts or crystals. The serum creatinine level is normal. A 24-hour urine collection yields 3.8 g of protein (&lt;150 mg/24 h), primarily of low molecular weight. He improves after corticosteroid therapy. He has more episodes of proteinuria over the next 4 years, which respond to corticosteroid therapy. A renal biopsy is performed. Which of the following is the most likely alteration in the glomeruli by light microscopy?`,
