        q: `A 19-year-old woman has had a fever and chills accompanied by right flank pain for the past 3 days. She has had two similar episodes during the past year. On physical examination, her temperature is 38.3&#176;C, her blood pressure is 152/94 mm Hg, and there is right costovertebral angle tenderness. Laboratory findings show a fasting serum glucose level of 77 mg/dL (70-110 mg/dL) and creatinine level of 1 mg/dL (0.6-1.2 mg/dL). Urinalysis shows no protein, RBCs, glucose, or ketones, but numerous WBCs are noted. Which of the following is the most useful test for diagnosis?`,
