        optionFeedback: [`Elevated serum potassium is not a paraneoplastic syndrome. Hypercalcemia, however, can be seen due to overproduction of parathyroid hormone-related protein (PTHrP).`,`The clinical and pathologic findings are classic for the clear cell variant of renal cell carcinoma. Some of these tumors produce erythropoietin, which can cause erythrocytosis or polycythemia. `,`Cushing syndrome is a paraneoplastic syndrome associated with small cell carcinoma of lung. It is caused by tumor cell production of an ACTH-like substance; this is not associated with renal cell carcinomas.`,`There is no evidence that the cells of renal cell carcinoma can produce hepcidin, which, if elevated, would be expected to produce the “anemia of chronic inflammation”.`,``],
        optionStyleType: `st-upper-alpha`,
