        ansText: `Rationale:- Familial papillary renal cell carcinomas are most often associated with activation of the MET   gene, which encodes a receptor for hepatocyte growth factor. Increased responses to this growth factor are thought to lead to tumorigenesis. This tumor tends to be multifocal and bilateral.   `,
